<TITLE> HC rules acting law secretary appointment illegal </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 18 (bdnews24.com)- The High Court Monday declared the appointment of acting law secretary Kazi Habibul Awal illegal. A High Court bench of Justices Shah Abu Nayeem Mominur Rahman and Shahidul Islam delivered the order on a writ petition, filed by retired district judge Md Aftab Uddin. Additional secretary of the law ministry, Kazi Habibul Awal, was appointed acting law secretary on June 28 last year. Md Aftab Uddin on July 8 filed a writ petition with the High Court challenging the validity of the appointment alleging irregularities in the appointment process. The High Court on July 8 issued rule nisi on the government and Habibul on why the appointment process was not illegal. After holding the final hearing on the writ petition, the Court on Monday declared the appointment of the acting law secretary illegal. The court ordered that the copy of the verdict be sent immediately to the ministry of establishment, the law adviser and the chief justice. bdnews24.
